# ORTEC ULTRA BU-014-050-100 alpha spectroscopy datasheet (Experiment 4)
# cross-check: Am-241 5.486 MeV alpha, 500 Angstrom (0.05 um) boron-
# implanted Si dead layer, 100 um Si depletion depth (= sensitive
# thickness). Datasheet states a 5 MeV alpha loses ~7 keV in the 500 A
# dead layer, and the example spectrum shows FWHM ~15 keV (guaranteed
# spec <14 keV) for the 5.486 MeV peak. Known geometry, known source
# energy, known material -- unlike Hitachi (guessed) or McNulty
# (CUPID-model-derived), this is a real vendor-specified device.
/random/setSeeds 24111 24112
/sim/particle alpha
/sim/sensitiveXY 1 mm
/sim/deadXY 1 mm
/sim/sensitiveThickness 100 um
/sim/deadThickness 0.05 um
/sim/incidentAngle 0 deg
/sim/sensitiveMaterial Si
/sim/deadMaterial Si
/sim/biasCrossSectionFactor 1
/sim/useCollectionModel true
/sim/carrierLifetime 1.0 ns
/sim/electricField 1000000 volt/m
/run/initialize
/run/reinitializeGeometry

/sim/energy 5.486 MeV
/sim/beamXY 1 mm
/sim/criticalCharge 150
/sim/verbose false

/run/beamOn 100000
